		"description": {
			"value": "<p><strong>No Action Cost</strong> </p><p>When you cast a spell using your @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.UeNCm9oElbQEXre6]{Bloodrager Spellcasting} feature, you can choose to make the spell trigger a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.JournalEntry.FEMWrKEyIrd0s6BT.JournalEntryPage.VJrA212Hv3sI9yQv]{wild surge}. If you roll a Wild Surge that references Sorcery Points, Metamagic, or otherwise requires you to be a sorcerer, you instead regain one use of @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.W6yKtk7Svvy9dIq9]{Rage}.</p><p></p><p><strong>Note: This ability is not automated in Foundry. You can find the wild surge tables in the compendium tab under Elkan 5e -&gt; Other -&gt; Elkan 5e Roll Tables.</strong> </p>",
